Salmonella osteomyelitis of the skull base.
 A case of skull base osteomyelitis caused by Salmonella is reported.
 The patient, a diabetic immunosuppressed man, had a insidious presentation of nasopharyngeal and cranial nerve findings.
 His radiologic studies showed a striking destruction of the skull base.
 He died despite antibiotic therapy.
 Relevant literature is discussed.
